
[1]motto

   MOT'TO, n. Primarily, a word; but more commonly, a sentence or phrase
   prefixed to an essay or discourse, containing the subject of it, or
   added to a device.

   In heraldry, the motto is carried in a scroll, alluding to the bearing
   or to the name of the bearer, or expressing some important idea.
